# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from your Supabase project settings: https://supabase.com/dashboard
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# OAuth Configuration (Optional - configured in Supabase Dashboard)
# These are NOT needed in your .env file as they are configured directly in Supabase
# But listed here for reference of what needs to be set up:

# Google OAuth (configure at https://console.cloud.google.com)
# - Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application type)
# - Add authorized JavaScript origins:
#   - http://localhost:3000 (for development)
#   - https://your-domain.com (for production)
# - Add authorized redirect URIs:
#   - https://your-project-id.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
# - Copy Client ID and Client Secret to Supabase Dashboard

# Apple OAuth (configure at https://developer.apple.com)
# - Create App ID with Sign in with Apple capability
# - Create Services ID for web authentication
# - Configure website URLs:
#   - Domain: your-project-id.supabase.co
#   - Return URL: https://your-project-id.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
# - Generate private key
# - Copy Team ID, Service ID, and Private Key to Supabase Dashboard

# Local Development (optional)
# For testing OAuth locally, you may need to use ngrok or similar tool
# to expose your localhost with HTTPS